BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:Etd09TjJUUb-X950tBbdH
SUMMARY:Book Presentation: “The Dream of Sor Juana Inés de la Cruz” by Elwi
	n L. Wirkala
DTSTAMP:20260406T013217Z
DTSTART:20260423T180000Z
DESCRIPTION:Elwin L. Wirkala\\\, a poet and translator from the state of Wa
	shington\\\, published in 2024 the book “The Dream of Sor Juana Inés de la
	 Cruz\\\,” which features an annotated translation of “Primero Sueño\\\,” 
	a poem by Sor Juana Inés de la Cruz that stands as one of the masterpieces
	 of Spanish-language poetry and a landmark in Mexican culture. \\nThrough 
	a translation of the poem accompanied by annotations\\\, commentary\\\, an
	d analysis\\\, Wirkala’s book offers both Spanish and English-speaking rea
	ders an accessible invitation to the most celebrated work of Sor Juana Iné
	s de la Cruz\\\, a leading figure of the Spanish Golden Age in the America
	s. \\nThe purpose of the book presentation is to promote the work of Sor J
	uana Inés de la Cruz through the perspective of a U.S.-based scholar\\\, t
	hereby fostering cultural ties between Mexico and the United States. \\n \
	\nPresenter (Interviewer):  \\nJorge López has been a member of the Mexica
	n Foreign Service since 2023. He currently serves as Consul of Documentati
	on of Mexico in Seattle\\\, where he provides consular assistance to Mexic
	an nationals residing in the states of Washington and Alaska.\n\nhttps://h
	ugohouse.org/event/_2026-04-23/\n\nFrom Hugo House
URL:https://hugohouse.org/event/_2026-04-23/
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:hugo-house
CATEGORIES:Hugo House
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
